20month%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20is%20looking%20to%20hear%20from%20New%20Yorkers%20concerned%20with%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living.%20%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%20by%20filling%20out%20this%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforms.gle%2FDMKXCqxwPmPDwpRE6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Equick%20form%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220db53fa5-31dd-46d2-a82c-37db107b91ca%5C%22%3ESticker%20shock%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20first%20arrived%20in%20the%20city%2C%20Kinnare%20spent%20%242%2C000%20on%20rent%20for%20a%20two-bedroom%20apartment%20in%20the%20Bedford-Stuyvesant%20neighborhood%20of%20Brooklyn%20that%20she%20also%20used%20as%20her%20art%20studio.%20Eventually%2C%20she%20moved%20in%20with%20two%20roommates%20and%20rented%20a%20separate%20studio%2C%20where%20she%20had%20more%20room%20to%20grow%20her%20craft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20she%20moved%20in%20with%20her%20partner%2C%20and%20spends%20about%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20her%20share%20of%20the%20%242%2C600%20rent%20for%20their%20Bed-Stuy%20loft%2C%20and%20another%20%241%2C700%20on%20her%20studio%20space%20in%20Dumbo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FM6h5S%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Choropleth%20map%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FM6h5S%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20she's%20steadily%20grown%20her%20art%20sales%20and%20income%2C%20which%20started%20around%20%2450%2C000%20a%20year%20when%20she%20first%20moved%20to%20the%20city%2C%20and%20last%20year%20exceeded%20%24100%2C000.%20That's%20in%20part%20because%20one%20of%20her%20products%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%2445%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.courtneykinnare.com%2Fpurse-hooks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epurse%20hook%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20took%20off%20late%20last%20year.%20She%20quickly%20sold%20out%20of%20her%20first%201%2C500%20hooks%2C%20made%20of%20metal%2C%20glass%2C%20abalone%20shell%2C%20and%20mother-of-pearl%2C%20and%20designed%20to%20hang%20a%20bag%20from%20a%20restaurant%20table%20or%20bar.%20She%20recently%20dropped%202%2C000%20more%20and%20hopes%20to%20make%20them%20a%20permanent%20part%20of%20her%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20her%20recent%20windfall%2C%20budgeting%20is%20tricky%20with%20an%20income%20that%20varies%20dramatically%20month%20to%20month.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20family%20money%20to%20fall%20back%20on%2C%20or%20anyone%20to%20ask%20to%20borrow%20money%20from%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20Kinnare's%20social%20life%2C%20especially%20with%20friends%20who%20work%20corporate%20jobs%20and%20like%20to%20go%20out.%20She%20says%20she%20skips%20dinners%20out%20and%20has%20made%20a%20concerted%20effort%20to%20surround%20herself%20with%20other%20artists%20who%20understand%20the%20reality%20of%20having%20an%20unreliable%20income%20and%20the%20lifestyle%20that%20comes%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20you%20blink%20your%20eyes%20and%20spend%20%24100%2C%20and%20you're%20like%2C%20what%20just%20happened%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20taken%20a%20lot%20of%20self-control%20to%20be%20able%20to%20find%20activities%20and%20things%20to%20do%20that%20don't%20require%20spending%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229504%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Courtney%20Kinnare%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F697bc2f6d3c7faef0ecd353f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226336%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJanice%20Chung%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20factoring%20in%20the%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20New%20York%20creative%20workers%20like%20Kinnare%20earn%20about%2023%25%20less%20than%20the%20national%20average%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnycfuture.org%2Fpdf%2FCUF_CreativeNY_Report_9.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20nonprofit%20Center%20for%20an%20Urban%20Future%20found.%20A%20decade%20ago%2C%20they%20earned%2015%25%20less%20than%20the%20average.%20Much%20of%20that%20has%20to%20do%20with%20pricier%20real%20estate.%20With%20tighter%20living%20quarters%20in%20the%20city%2C%20many%20artists%20rent%20a%20separate%20studio%20space%20to%20work%20on%20their%20craft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20a%20studio%20space%20with%20enough%20room%20and%20natural%20light%20was%20even%20harder%20than%20finding%20an%20apartment%2C%20Kinnare%20says.%20When%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20move%20out%20of%20one%20studio%20on%20short%20notice%2C%20she%20struggled%20to%20find%20anything%20affordable%20on%20the%20market%20that%20had%20a%20window.%20So%20she%20resorted%20to%20messaging%20artists%20she%20didn't%20know%20on%20Instagram%2C%20asking%20for%20their%20landlords'%20contact%20information.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20really%2C%20really%20fast%20game%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20be%20on%20top%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22123c6a67-f9ec-4c4b-b0ea-fab9afc2234e%5C%22%3EAn%20investment%20in%20the%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKinnare%20sees%20the%20high%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20New%20York%20City%20as%20an%20investment%20in%20her%20career%20that%2C%20so%20far%2C%20is%20paying%20off.%20She%20thinks%20it's%20easier%20to%20break%20into%20the%20art%20world%20than%20it%20was%20in%20LA%2C%20where%20she%20felt%20more%20professionally%20isolated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20art%20scene%20here%20is%20a%20lot%20more%20diverse%20and%20approachable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20frequenting%20galleries%20a%20lot%20more%2C%20going%20to%20openings%2C%20going%20to%20shows%2C%20being%20in%20places%20where%20I%20want%20to%20be%2C%20networking%20and%20seeing%20and%20having%20the%20chance%20to%20talk%20to%20some%20of%20these%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20exposure%20here%20has%20been%20tenfold%20compared%20to%20what%20I've%20been%20used%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229504%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Courtney%20Kinnare%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F697bc35ad3c7faef0ecd3550%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226336%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJanice%20Chung%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20she%20signed%20with%20a%20gallery%20after%20meeting%20their%20owners%20at%20a%20design%20fair%20and%20has%20since%20shown%20her%20work%20at%20multiple%20fairs%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20costs%20of%20breaking%20into%20the%20most%20dynamic%20creative%20scene%20in%20the%20country%20are%20high%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20creatives%20aren't%20making%20it.%20Many%20artists%20who%20left%20New%20York%20when%20COVID%20hit%20haven't%20returned.%20The%20number%20of%20New%20Yorkers%20working%20in%20the%20creative%20economy%2C%20including%20self-employed%20people%2C%20has%20dropped%20by%20about%206%25%20since%202019%2C%20the%20Center%20for%20an%20Urban%20Future%20found.%20The%20city%20has%20lost%20nearly%20one-fifth%20of%20its%20dancers%20and%20film%20and%20video%20editors.%20More%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20its%20fashion%20designers%20have%20disappeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKinnare%20feels%20like%20one%20of%20the%20lucky%20ones.%20Her%20sales%20and%20social%20media%20following%20are%20growing%2C%20and%20she%20finally%20has%20some%20savings.%20One%20of%20her%20goals%20for%202026%20is%20to%20give%20herself%20one%20day%20a%20week%20when%20she%20doesn't%20open%20her%20laptop%20or%20step%20inside%20the%20studio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20l