26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20In%20turn%2C%20he's%20made%20the%20choice%20to%20take%20on%20%26quot%3Bthe%20world%20as%20it%20is%2C%20not%20wait%20around%20for%20a%20world%20we%20wish%20it%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarney%20is%20walking%20a%20fine%20line.%20He%20is%20right%20that%20the%20US%20is%20no%20longer%20as%20reliable%20a%20partner%20as%20it%20once%20was%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20security%2C%20and%20trade.%20And%20as%20much%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-canada-economy-tariffs-trade-war-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20turned%20the%20divide%20into%20a%20chasm%2C%20the%20fracture%20has%20been%20forming%20for%20years%2C%20as%20both%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20administrations%20in%20the%20US%20have%20taken%20a%20more%20protectionist%20stance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Canada%20can't%20just%20walk%20away.%20Exports%20account%20for%20a%20third%20of%20Canada's%20GDP%2C%20and%20more%20than%2075%25%20of%20its%20exports%20go%20to%20the%20US.%20By%20comparison%2C%20exports%20are%20about%20one-tenth%20of%20the%20US's%20GDP%2C%20and%20around%2016%25%20of%20its%20exports%20go%20to%20Canada.%20Many%20of%20the%20two%20countries'%20biggest%20industrial%20sectors%2C%20including%20automotives%20and%20energy%2C%20are%20almost%20irreversibly%20interwoven.%20The%20uncertainty%20emanating%20from%20the%20US%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyale-budget-report-canada-gdp-suffer-most-trump-tariff-damage-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebig%20impact%20on%20Canada's%3C%2Fa%3E%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20as%20the%20saying%20goes%2C%20when%20the%20US%20catches%20a%20cold%2C%20Canada%20gets%20the%20flu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20short-term%20impetus%20to%20keep%20relations%20amicable.%20The%20US-Mexico-Canada%20trade%20deal%20(formerly%20known%20as%20NAFTA)%20is%20up%20for%20review%20mid-year%2C%20and%20the%20US%2C%20thanks%20to%20its%20sheer%20size%2C%20has%20more%20leverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20prime%20minister's%20in%20an%20impossible%20situation.%20It%20is%20incredibly%20challenging%20for%20any%20Canadian%20on%20the%20international%20side%20right%20now%20to%20both%20vigorously%20defend%20our%20economy%20and%20to%20do%20that%20without%20escalating%20an%20already%20volatile%20relationship%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dan%20Kelly%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Canadian%20Federation%20of%20Independent%20Business.%20%26quot%3BThe%20pope%20himself%2C%20I%20think%2C%20would%20struggle%20to%20find%20the%20patience%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20US%20administration%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ECanada%20is%20trying%20to%20reduce%20its%20reliance%20on%20the%20US%20through%20a%20series%20of%20policies%20aimed%20at%20growing%20and%20integrating%20its%20domestic%20economy.%20The%20federal%20government%20removed%20internal%20trade%20barriers%20that%20prevented%20goods%20and%20even%20workers%20from%20flowing%20between%20provinces.%20The%20IMF%20estimates%20that%20fully%20eliminating%20them%20would%20boost%20real%20Canadian%20GDP%20by%207%25.%20Many%20Canadian%20consumers%20are%20opting%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmade-in-canada-directory-surges-traffic-trump-tariffs-threats-boycott-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuy%20Canadian%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20possible.%20Under%20Carney%2C%20the%20country%20established%20the%20Major%20Projects%20Office%20as%20part%20of%20a%20push%20to%20advance%20nation-building%20ventures%20and%20streamline%20regulatory%20approvals%20for%20ambitious%20programs%20in%20mining%2C%20energy%2C%20ports%2C%20and%20rail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20government%20isn't%20trying%20to%20just%20invest%2C%20they're%20trying%20to%20catalyze%20and%20incentivize%20private%20money%20to%20come%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Stillo%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20steps%20in%20the%20right%20direction%2C%20but%20the%20major%20projects%20will%20take%20years%20to%20build.%20This%20is%20a%20long-term%20undertaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20high-talent%20workers.%20We're%20the%20most%20educated%20in%20the%20OECD.%20We%20have%20real%20innovation%20in%20areas%20like%20AI%20and%20quantum%20computing%2C%20and%20we%20have%20natural%20resources%20%E2%80%94%20critical%20minerals%2C%20LNG%2C%20oil%20and%20gas%20%E2%80%94%20most%20countries%20would%20absolutely%20love%20to%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Matthew%20Holmes%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20public%20policy%20at%20the%20Canadian%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20all%20the%20preconditions%20to%20be%20an%20energy%20superpower%20and%20a%20major%20player%20economically%2C%20but%20we%20need%20to%20get%20our%20domestic%20economy%20fundamentals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelly%20tells%20me%20about%20a%20third%20of%20CFIB's%20members%2C%20which%20are%20small-%20and%20medium-sized%20businesses%2C%20have%20started%20to%20do%20more%20business%20internationally%20in%20countries%20beyond%20the%20US%2C%20and%20a%20third%20are%20doing%20more%20internal%20trade.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankofcanada.ca%2Fpublications%2Fbos%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20business%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Bank%20of%20Canada%20found%20that%20sentiment%20remains%20%26quot%3Bsubdued%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20firms'%20overall%20outlook%20has%20improved%20slightly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20problem%20Canada%20faces%20is%20that%20any%20move%20it%20makes%20to%20cultivate%20ties%20elsewhere%20may%20elicit%20an%20outsize%20reaction%20from%20its%20neighbors%20to%20the%20south.%20Just%20look%20at%20its%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-courting-asia-after-a-year-of-trade-trump-tariffs-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade%20negotiations%20with%20China%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Carney%20visited%20China%20in%20January%20and%20subsequently%20announced%20that%20Canada%20would%20allow%2049%2C000%20Chinese%20electric%20vehicles%20into%20the%20Canadian%20market%20at%20a%206.1%25%20tariff%20rate%2C%20while%20China%20agreed%20to%20lower%20tariffs%20on%20Canadian%20canola%20seed.%20When%20Trump%20caught%20wind%20of%20it%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-tariffs-china-trade-deal-donald-trump-mark-carney-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethreatened%20to%20put%20100%25%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Canadian%20goods%20coming%20into%20the%20US.%20Canada%20has%20tried%20to%20calm%20the%20situation%2C%20emphasizing%20that%20it's%20not%20entering%20a%20free%20trade%20agreement%20with%20China%2C%20it's%20just%20settling%20some%20preexisting%20disputes.%20The%20tit-for-tat%20also%20comes%20as%20Canadian%20oil%20sales%20in%20China%20surge%2C%20as%20it%20pushes%20into%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20running%20into%20the%20arms%20of%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Julian%20Karaguesian%2C%20a%20course%20lecturer%20in%20McGill%20University's%20economics%20department.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20just%20looking%20to%20take%20a%20couple%20of%20eggs%20out%20of%20this%20basket%20and%20spread%20them%20around%20the%20world.%20And%20China's%20the%20largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%20after%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECanada%20has%20trade%20opportunities%20outside%20the%20US%20and%20has%20set%20a%20goal%20to%20double%20non-US%20exports%20over%20the%20next%20decade.%20It%20already%20has%20a%20robust%20set%20of%20free%20trade%20agreements%20and%20is%20the%20only%20G7%20nation%20to%20have%20them%20with%20all%20other%20G7%20members.%20It's%20also%20likely%20looking%20toward%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fr-south-american-trade-bloc-gains-strength-misses-eu-deal-2017-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eand%20MERCOSUR%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20trade%20bloc%20in%20South%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommerce%20Secretary%20Howard%20Lutnick%