sinsider.com%2Fsydney-australia-most-instagrammable-vacation-spot-photos-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emy%20home%20in%20Sydney%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20never%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20I%20had%20toyed%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-across-country-live-with-parents-drawbacks-regret-benefits-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emoving%20back%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20place%20I%20had%20not%20lived%20since%20I%20was%207%20years%20old.%20I'd%20even%20made%20a%20couple%20of%20attempts%20at%20it%2C%20but%20the%20comfortable%20pull%20of%20family%20and%20more%20than%2025%20years%20of%20life%20in%20the%20US%20always%20lured%20me%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20extending%20my%20trip%20week%20by%20week%20turned%20into%20deciding%20to%20stay%2C%20I%20assumed%20slotting%20back%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-never-do-in-australia-from-woman-lives-there%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elife%20in%20Australia%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20the%20easiest%20move%20of%20my%20life.%20After%20all%2C%20I%20was%20used%20to%20adjusting%20to%20a%20new%20environment.%20My%20father's%20job%20in%20the%20film%20industry%20meant%20I%20spent%20my%20childhood%20moving%20frequently%20(13%20different%20schools%20in%20multiple%20cities%20and%20countries).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESurely%20moving%20back%20home%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-back-hometown-closer-parents-grandparents-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efeel%20as%20comforting%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20slipping%20on%20a%20well-worn%2C%20much-loved%20cardigan.%20I%20was%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220bf8a59b-b142-4754-b0a9-da84f344ea43%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20unexpected%20culture%20shock%20of%20coming%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20thought%20I%20would%20experience%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freverse-culture-shocks-americans-us-after-living-abroad-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eculture%20shock%20moving%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20to%20Australia%2C%20but%20that%20was%20exactly%20what%20happened.%20All%20my%20years%20overseas%20meant%20I%20had%20missed%20large%20parts%20of%20general%20knowledge%2C%20I%20didn't%20understand%20cultural%20references%20or%20sayings%2C%20and%20I%20found%20Australian%20politics%20completely%20befuddling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20still%20sounded%20Australian%2C%20a%20quick%20conversation%2C%20which%20inexplicably%20always%20started%20with%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20did%20you%20go%20to%20high%20school%3F%26quot%3B%20quickly%20established%20I%20was%20not%20from%20here.%20After%20being%20viewed%20as%20a%20foreigner%20my%20whole%20life%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20was%20now%20viewed%20as%20a%20foreigner%20in%20Australia%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20I%20realized%20with%20surprise%20that%20I%20was%20culturally%20very%20American.%20All%20the%20things%20I%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthese-uncomfortable-deeds-could-pay-off-forever-2015-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etaken%20for%20granted%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20(convenience%2C%20customer%20service%2C%20and%20affordability)%20just%20didn't%20exist%20in%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e0395047-4531-463b-8d8f-0607d08c7ad2%5C%22%3EI%20had%20to%20do%20some%20life%20adjustments%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20the%20daily%20frustrations%20of%20not%20being%20able%20to%20get%20a%20coffee%20past%203%20p.m.%20(or%20before%207%20a.m.)%2C%20no%20salad%20bars%20or%20real%20Mexican%20food%2C%20and%20the%20expense%20of%20absolutely%20everything%20(Sydney%20is%20Australia's%20most%20expensive%20city).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECultural%20norms%20were%20an%20even%20bigger%20adjustment.%20Handshakes%20for%20acquaintances%20and%20bear%20hugs%20for%20friends%20(standard%20etiquette%20in%20the%20US)%20were%20replaced%20with%20one%20or%20two%20kisses%20to%20the%20side%20of%20(n